<title>THE SPORTS TRAINING AS A STRESS FACTOR</title>
<base target="_blank">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<table border="0" width="570">
  <tr>
    <td><p align="center"><strong><font size="2">THE SPORTS TRAINING AS A STRESS FACTOR</font></strong></p>
    <p align="center"><font size="2">D.Dasheva</font></p>
    <p align="center"><font size="2">National Sports Academy, Department of Sports Training,<br>
    Sofia, Bulgaria</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">The adaptation toward the physical and psychological
    stress is the main factor for obtaining the high sports performance. The distinctive
    features of contemporary sports are closely related to the theory of Hans Selye about
    stress, stress factors and stress training. The sports training is the basic factor for
    widening and perfecting the adaptation mechanisms in given direction as well as in similar
    adaptation mechanisms. While developing the sport result we realize the adaptation process
    whose material expression is the systematical-structural trace.</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">At the present the attention of sports specialists is
    concentrated toward a search for new forms of influence and organization of the training
    process within the framework of the physiologically possible. The practice itself needs
    the application of the stress training for heightening the human possibilities. The
    effectiveness of their utilization will be measured with the immediate and commutative
    effect of adaptation. The specificity of the adaptation process supposes the introduction
    of measures for the training stress load i.e &quot;unit of the training load&quot; and
    &quot;threshold of adaptation&quot;. The problem is very complex and multidimensional and
    its dealing presuppose an answer to following important questions:</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">Which are the precise criterions of the stress training?
    If any.</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">What is the algorithm of application of the stress
    training?</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">What will be the content (exercises, volume and
    intensity) of the stress training?</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">When their application will be fortunate?</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">What is the individual stress threshold?</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">Some practical investigations (Dasheva, D, 1991) allowed
    to made certain suppositions and recommendations about the principal positions of their
    application during the training process in a middle and long aspect. </font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2"><b>The first</b>. The specific program including the
    stress training is the keystone for creating the psychological stability and work-capacity
    during the anxiety situations as the sport competition.</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2"><b>The second</b>. The stress training needs the high
    mobilization of structural and energetic possibilities and respectively the high
    work-capacity during the training process.</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2"><b>The third.</b> The stress training is related to the
    i.e &quot; threshold of adaptive changes&quot;. This is the moment, that the stimulus able
    to provoke a &quot;shaking&quot; effect on the different bodily function must be changed
    in intention to produce the new reactions and posteriori new structural changes.</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2"><b>The four</b>. The stress training is connected to the
    individual stress range for each athlete and individual optimal stress load, that provoke
    the adequate adaptive changes. This range widens constantly during the training process.
    At the last (but not last), the application of the stress training depends of the
    qualification and level of the sportsmen, the specificity of the motor activity and the
    stage of preparation. </font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">In conclusion, we must marked that there have not
    &quot;prescriptions&quot; for the stress training, stress micro, meso and macro cycles.
    There are some common principles and regularities whose must be adapted to the specific
    tasks of the training process.</font></p>
    <p align="center"><font size="2"><b>BIBLIOGRAPHY</b></font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">1. Dasheva, D. Stress and stress influences in the
    preparation of the top level basketball players. Dissertation, NSA, 1991. </font></td>
  </tr>
</table>
